alert.note: Alert for Eastern Aleutians (Alaska) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued October 28 at 4:18PM AKDT until October 29 at 1:00AM AKDT by NWS Anchorage
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 AM AKDT SATURDAY... * WHAT...West winds 50 to 70 mph with gusts up to 90 mph expected. * WHERE...Eastern Aleutians. * WHEN...Until 1 AM AKDT Saturday. * IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property, and cause power outages. Travel will be difficult. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A deepening low pressure system moves north of the Aleutian Chain through tonight. Hurricane force winds along the Eastern Aleutians will quickly diminish tomorrow morning as the low moves towards the Gulf of Alaska.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind. Prepare for the possibility of widespread power outages. Use caution if you must drive.
